## 2026-04-07 - Global unmodified keyboard shortcuts trigger unexpected mutations
- Changed the token-list "new token" shortcut from bare `N` to `Cmd/Ctrl+N` in the shared shortcut registry so list focus no longer intercepts plain `n` while users are navigating or preparing to search.
- Tightened `handleListKeyDown` so bulk delete on `Backspace` only fires when multi-select is active, there is an actual selection, and keyboard focus is still on a token/group row. The create-token handler now reuses the same focused row lookup instead of re-reading `document.activeElement`.
